First note that a negative divided by a negative is positive.  To divide the decimals, you can eliminate the decimal points by multiplying numerator and denominator by 100:

\[
-4.11\div(-0.12)
=\frac{-4.11}{-0.12}
=\frac{-4.11\times100}{-0.12\times100}
=\frac{-411}{-12}
=\frac{411}{12}
=34.25.
\]

Answer: 34.25.
